summary: English cricketer Will Jacks made history in the Indian Premier League (IPL) with an astonishing century that shocked the cricketing world. Leading Royal Challengers Bangalore (RCB) to victory against Gujarat Titans, Jacks smashed 100 runs off just 41 balls, with an incredible 10 sixes. His rapid scoring from 50 to 100 in only 10 balls left even the legendary Virat Kohli astounded and laughing in disbelief. Jacks' batting assault left Rashid Khan, a top-ranked bowler, in ruins. Kohli praised Jacks for his phenomenal performance, revealing a pre-match conversation where he was ready for three runs only to witness Jacks' determination to hit every ball for six. The young English star's heroics not only earned RCB a significant win but also marked the first century of his IPL career.

summary: Interest rates in Australia are expected to continue rising, with experts predicting the Reserve Bank of Australia (RBA) will raise the cash rate to 5.1%. This will put pressure on banks, who may need to consider critical decisions when rates eventually fall. name: Al Maktoum International Airport
summary: Dubai is investing heavily in its aviation infrastructure with the construction of the world's largest airport, Al Maktoum International Airport, which will cost $53 billion and be a major hub for Emirates Airlines. The new terminal, costing $35 billion, will be completed within a decade and will consolidate Dubai's international airport operations, moving them from the current hub. This expansion project aims to establish Dubai as a global aviation hub and accommodate future growth in air travel demand. The Al Maktoum International Airport will feature state-of-the-art facilities, including a vast duty-free shopping area, luxurious lounges, and efficient baggage handling systems. The airport's strategic location will strengthen Dubai's connectivity to key global destinations and further solidify its position as a major player in the global aviation industry.
